Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them onto
a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved and deseeded) and discard the core
and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the @British chicken breasts{2} into the pan and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned, ~{5%minutes} each side.

Once browned, lay the chicken onto another baking tray. Add the sliced pepper,
drizzle with a little more @olive oil{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven
until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. It's cooked when no
> longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby cucumber{1}(trimmed), then halve lengthways. Cut
lengthways into roughly 1cm wide strips, then cut into 1cm pieces widthways.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto your board, face-down. Slice lengthways into 1cm thick slices -
you'll fan it out later.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{30%milliliters},
@sugar{2%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{2%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your dressing aside.

When the potatoes, pepper and chicken have roasted, remove them from the oven
and allow to cool a little.

Once cooled, add the roasted veg to the dressing bowl with the chopped cucumber
and @baby leaf mix{50%grams}.

Toss together, then taste and add more @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Pop the chicken onto a #chopping board{} and slice widthways into 1cm thick
slices.

Share the salad between your #serving bowls{}, then crumble over the
@Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} and sprinkle with the
@pumpkin seeds{15%grams}.

Fan the sliced avocado out on top of the salad, top with the sliced chicken and
finish by drizzling over the @pesto{32%grams}.

> Mix the pesto with a little olive oil to get a more drizzling consistency
> if you'd like.

Enjoy!